# Supabase Configuration
# Required for job application functionality
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# EmailJS Configuration (Optional)
# Required only if you want email notifications for job applications
# Get these values from your EmailJS dashboard at https://www.emailjs.com/
# If not configured, job applications will still be saved to Supabase
# but no email notifications will be sent

# Note: Replace the placeholder values in src/config/emailjs.ts with your actual EmailJS credentials:
# - serviceId: Your EmailJS service ID
# - templateId: Your EmailJS template ID  
# - publicKey: Your EmailJS public key

# Example EmailJS setup:
# 1. Go to https://www.emailjs.com/
# 2. Create an account and verify your email
# 3. Create a new service (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)
# 4. Create an email template with the variables listed in src/config/emailjs.ts
# 5. Get your Public Key from the Integration page
# 6. Update the values in src/config/emailjs.ts